Title: The Action Principle in Epstein Glaser Renormalization and
  Renormalization of the S-Matrix in $\phi^4$-Theory
Authors: G. Pinter
Comments: 32 pages, added reference, corrected typos and changed content
Report-no: DESY 99-168
Journal-ref: Annalen Phys. 10 (2001) 333-363
\\
  A formula describing finite renormalizations is derived in the Epstein-Glaser
formalism and an explicit calculation of finite counterterms in $\Phi
^4$-theory is performed. The Zimmermann identities and the action principle for
changes of parameters in the interaction are presented independent of the
adiabatic limit.
